# Description

Fixes https://github.com/hub4j/github-api/issues/1171

* Allows users to create discussions when creating or updating a new release
* Adds tests for the creation, update and deletion of releases (See `GHReleaseTest`)
* Removes ignored code

The [documentation](https://docs.github.com/en/rest/reference/repos#create-a-release) allows to set the `discussion_category_name` value when creating or updating a release to create an associated discussion with the release.

This looks like this (using the test repository you provided)
 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/921666/121438803-f9475600-c984-11eb-8cef-fa01b3d79902.png)

Here is a snippet of code that shows the added behavior:
```
package org.kohsuke.github;

import java.io.IOException;
import java.util.UUID;

public class JlengrandRelease {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException, InterruptedException {
        // In case the category doesn't exist : Status: 404 Not Found {"message":"Discussion could not be created. Make sure you passed a valid category name.","documentation_url":"https://docs.github.com/rest/reference/repos#create-a-release"}
        // Discussions need to be activated and setup
        // see here for default categories: https://docs.github.com/en/discussions/managing-discussions-for-your-community/managing-categories-for-discussions-in-your-repository

        GitHub gitHub = GitHub.connect();

        GHRepository r = gitHub.getRepository("jlengrand/testCreateRelease");

        String tagName = UUID.randomUUID().toString();
        String tagName1 = tagName + "-first";
        String tagName2 = tagName + "-second";

        GHRelease rel = r.createRelease(tagName1)
                .name("release-" + tagName1)
                .prerelease(false)
                .categoryName("announcements")
                .create();

        // then updates

        GHRelease rel2 = r.createRelease(tagName2)
                .name("release-" + tagName2)
                .prerelease(false)
                .create();

        rel2.update().prerelease(false).categoryName("Q&A").update();

    }
}
```

which:
* creates a first release with announcement
* creates then a second release with announcement. Updates that release and creates the announcement.

